Package de.unihannover.se.iviewxjava.iviewx.eyetracker Description

Contains the SMI IViewX SDK specific configuration and receiver classes.

The manager classes handle connecting and configuring the eyetracking server. This package also includes the receiver implementations for use with the eyetracking core library.

Note that none of these classes should be created by the user. The IViewX class handles the singleton creation of these classes and provides static methods to access them for use in your program.

Also note that none of these classes are intended to be used concurrently. If you need concurrent access to the eyetracking receiver, you should use ETStreamService in conjunction with one of the receivers provided by the IViewX class.
